&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Envoy Global is a proven innovator in the global immigration space. Our mission combines our industry-leading tech platform with holistic service to streamline, simplify and expedite the immigration process for employers and individuals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Business Development Representative (BDR)&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;with Envoy Global, Inc.&lt;/em&gt; you will help to contribute to our continued growth by supporting our&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;fun and dynamic&lt;/em&gt; Sales Team. This is an excellent opportunity for an enthusiastic, highly-motivated, individual to join an extremely successful sales team within a rapidly growing organization! There is a direct path of advancement to an Account Executive role after a successful performance as a BDR.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Business Development Representatives enjoy the flexibility of remote sales work, backed by ongoing virtual training and a highly collaborative, supportive team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uncovering, qualifying, and building the sales opportunity pipeline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sourcing and targeting new customers by cold calling via phone and email&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applying creative lead generation tactics to uncover potential sales prospects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualifying leads by connecting with potential clients and identifying decision makers at the Executive and C-level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gaining commitment from prospects to virtually meet with an Account Executive via a web-based presentation to demonstrate our product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining records of all interactions with qualified prospects using Salesforce.com&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You May Need to be Successful:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant sales experience&amp;nbsp;or natural flair for honest sales, with integrity and an excellent ability to build rapport, with sincerity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong desire to gain hands-on sales experience including effective targeting, lead generation, and relationship development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written + verbal communication, and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-energy, results-oriented personality with a positive attitude and approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to quickly learn complex subjects and communicate them in a simple manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with one or a combination of sales system tools is a plus, such as Salesforce, Hubspot, Outreach, Zoominfo, etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Salary + Commission&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Annual Base Salary: $60,000&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Cash Range with Target Commission Opportunity: $60,000-$75,000&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Notice at Collection for California Applicants:&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.envoyglobal.com/notice-at-collection-for-ca-applicants&quot;&gt;http://www.envoyglobal.com/notice-at-collection-for-ca-applicants&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;#LI-REMOTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Envoy Global is a proven innovator in the global immigration space. Our mission combines our industry-leading tech platform with holistic service to streamline, simplify and expedite the immigration process for employers and individuals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a detail-oriented &lt;strong&gt;CMS Configuration Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; with 3–4 years of experience in application configuration using &lt;strong&gt;XML, SQL, and PDF-based form development&lt;/strong&gt;. The ideal candidate will play a key role in configuring, enhancing, and supporting CMS applications in a release-driven environment.&amp;nbsp;This role is primarily focused on &lt;strong&gt;application configuration, system support, and release management&lt;/strong&gt;, with &lt;strong&gt;limited development exposure in .NET technologies&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As our&amp;nbsp; CMS Configuration Engineer, you will be required to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and maintain CMS configurations using XML-based frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and support web application components within the CMS platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and automate PDF based Forms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write, optimize, and maintain SQL queries, scripts, and stored procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product, QA, and engineering teams to support feature releases and enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze CMS application behavior and identify UI/system limitations, recommending improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support release activities, including deployments, patches, and hotfixes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve production issues in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure configuration quality, performance optimization, and adherence to best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in review processes and contribute to continuous improvement initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with platform/product teams in a release-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and support fullstack (backend and frontend) &amp;nbsp;components using .NET technologies (C#, ASP.NET)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To apply for this role, you should possess the following skills, experience and qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–4 years of experience in application configuration and support roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong hands-on experience with XML-based configurations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good working knowledge of SQL (queries, joins, stored procedures)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in developing or managing PDF-based forms/templates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of web application architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to release/support environments and defect management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving and analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a cross-functional, fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-to-Have Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to .NET technologies (C#, ASP.NET)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with enterprise CMS platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with CI/CD or release management tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in product-based or platform engineering environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Envoy Global is a proven innovator in the global immigration space. Our mission combines our industry-leading tech platform with holistic service to streamline, simplify and expedite the immigration process for employers and individuals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corporate Paralegal – Envoy Global (U.S.)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; United States (Remote)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At &lt;strong&gt;Envoy Global&lt;/strong&gt;, we’re on a mission to deliver the future of global mobility—empowering companies and talent around the world with innovative technology, exceptional service, and a commitment to excellence. Our in‑house legal team plays a key role in helping us scale responsibly, operate with integrity, and support our teams with clarity and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Corporate Paralegal&lt;/strong&gt; who is detail‑driven, proactive, and excited to grow within a collaborative, high‑performing legal team. If you’re passionate about organization, precision, and supporting meaningful work across a fast‑moving business, this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;⭐ What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft, proofread, and support review of contracts, NDAs, corporate filings, and routine legal correspondence using approved templates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compare document versions, run redlines, and summarize changes to support efficient attorney review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage legal document repositories, version control, naming conventions, and access permissions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support contract execution by monitoring signature workflows and ensuring accurate storage of finalized documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track contracts, renewals, and corporate filings; maintain dashboards and proactively flag deadlines and action items&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide legal operations support, including invoice review, scheduling, intake of legal requests, and meeting notes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with internal stakeholders to gather facts, documents, and timelines and consolidate information for legal matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct legal research and prepare concise summaries with citations and practical business impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support corporate governance, compliance, and due‑diligence activities while handling sensitive information with discretion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🌟About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re an organized, curious, self‑motivated professional who takes pride in delivering precise, high‑quality work. You enjoy being a central partner to a team, gaining exposure across legal operations, and growing your expertise in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contract lifecycle management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corporate governance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legal research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Workflow efficiency and operational excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 4 years’ experience as a paralegal, ideally supporting commercial or corporate legal matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project‑management skills, with the ability to manage a high volume of contracts and contribute to strategic legal initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in‑house and/or within a large law firm, with a solid understanding of business‑focused legal support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience drafting, reviewing, and redlining contracts, including NDAs, commercial agreements, and other routine legal documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re comfortable working independently, confident in handling routine tasks, and thoughtful about when to seek guidance. You value clear communication, collaboration, and continuous learning—and you’re excited to build your career with a supportive, innovative in‑house legal team.&lt;/p&gt;
